---
import DefaultLayout from '@/layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 12, 2026';
---

<DefaultLayout
  title="Terms of Use — FirstHomeGuide.ca"
  description="Terms governing your use of FirstHomeGuide.ca — a free educational resource for Canadian first-time home buyers."
>
  <section class="section-padding container max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xxl leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
      Terms of Use
    </h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 leading-relaxed">
      By accessing or using FirstHomeGuide.ca (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), you agree to these
      Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-legal mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed md:text-base">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">1. About the Site</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          FirstHomeGuide.ca is a free educational resource for Canadian first-time home
          buyers, operated by LendCity (FSRA Brokerage Licence #12728) under Mortgage
          Architects. Content is provided for general informational purposes only.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">2. Not financial, legal, or tax advice</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Nothing on the Site constitutes financial, legal, tax, mortgage, real estate, or
          investment advice. Calculators and tools use general formulas and assumptions and
          do not account for your personal circumstances. Always consult a licensed
          professional before making a home-buying, financial, legal, or tax decision. See
          our full{' '}
          <a href="/disclaimer" class="underline underline-offset-4">disclaimer</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">3. Accuracy and updates</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We make reasonable efforts to keep content accurate and up to date with Canadian
          federal, provincial, and territorial rules. Programs, rates, tax rules, and CMHC
          premiums change frequently. We do not warrant that all content is current, complete,
          or error-free. Confirm details with the relevant government body or a licensed
          professional before acting.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">4. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>Use the Site for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable law.</li>
          <li>Scrape, harvest, or mass-download content other than through our RSS feed, <code>/llms.txt</code>, or <code>/sitemap.xml</code> endpoints.</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Site, its servers, or related systems.</li>
          <li>Introduce malware, run denial-of-service attacks, or otherwise interfere with the Site.</li>
          <li>Impersonate any person or entity, or misrepresent your affiliation with any person or entity, when submitting a form or booking a call.</li>
          <li>Use the Site&rsquo;s email-sending features (e.g., &ldquo;share this article&rdquo;) to send spam or unsolicited commercial messages.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">5. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          All content, branding, logos, and original graphics on the Site are the property of
          FirstHomeGuide.ca, LendCity, or their respective licensors, and are protected by
          Canadian and international copyright and trademark law. You may link to pages on the
          Site and quote short excerpts with attribution. You may not republish substantial
          portions of the Site without written permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">6. Third-party links</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Site links to government pages, lender sites, and other resources operated by
          third parties. We do not control and are not responsible for the content, accuracy,
          or privacy practices of those sites.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">7. Booking a call</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Booking a call through the Site connects you with a licensed mortgage professional
          at LendCity. Calls are complimentary and come with no obligation. Any subsequent
          mortgage application or agreement is governed by separate terms provided by LendCity
          at that time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">8. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Site is provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo; basis.
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, express or
          implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
          non-infringement, and accuracy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">9. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, FirstHomeGuide.ca, LendCity, and their
          contributors are not liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or
          punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of the Site or reliance on
          any content. Our total aggregate liability for any claim relating to the Site is
          limited to CAD $100.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You agree to indemnify and hold harmless FirstHomeGuide.ca, LendCity, and their
          affiliates from any claim, loss, or expense (including reasonable legal fees)
          arising from your misuse of the Site or breach of these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">11. Governing law</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the Province of Ontario and the federal laws
          of Canada applicable therein, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. You
          agree to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Ontario for any dispute arising
          out of or relating to these Terms or the Site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">12. Changes to these Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at
          the top of the page reflects the most recent change. Continued use of the Site after
          changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">13. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about these Terms? Reach us through the{' '}
          <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-4">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
